knowledge_graph.title: Squirrel
knowledge_graph.description: Squirrels are members of the family Sciuridae, a family that includes small or medium-sized rodents. The squirrel family includes tree squirrels, ground squirrels, and flying squirrels. Squirrels are indigenous to the Americas, Eurasia, and Africa, and were introduced by humans to Australia.

related_questions.question: What do squirrels like to eat the most?
related_questions.snippet: Some of their favorite foods include acorns, walnuts, hickory nuts and Osage orange fruits. They may also feed on wild tree fruits, nuts, and tree buds when food is scarce later in winter.
related_questions.title: What Do Squirrels Eat? Facts About Their Diet | Terminix

related_questions.question: Are squirrels intelligent?
related_questions.snippet: Squirrels exhibit remarkable intelligence, displaying cunning behaviors in their daily activities. Their cognitive abilities include problem-solving, memory retention, and adaptability to various environments. Research reveals squirrels' adeptness in locating hidden food caches, utilizing spatial memory efficiently.
related_questions.title: Are Squirrels Smart? Unlocking The Mysteries Of Squirrel Intelligence

related_questions.question: Are squirrels friendly animals?
related_questions.snippet: Being wild animals, squirrels always pose a risk of biting or scratching humans,6 even inadvertently, and especially if they become too comfortable and grab food from their hosts.
related_questions.title: Do Squirrels Remember Humans? - Treehugger

related_questions.question: What to do if you see a squirrel?
related_questions.snippet: Leave the squirrel alone, so they can find their way out. (They can jump from a second-story window onto a lawn without harming themselves, but don't let them jump onto concrete.)
